label: University of Pennsylvania Ms. Codex 694: Doctrinale
attribution: Provided by the University of Pennsylvania Libraries
description:
Summary: Fragment of the Doctrinale (incomplete at the beginning), with extensive marginal commentary and annotations.
        Language: 
        Support: parchment
        Extent: 
        Collation: 
        Layout: Written in 38 long lines in dark brown ink; ruled in ink; prickings visible.
        Script: Written in a Gothic book script by a single hand, with marginal commentary in several additional hands that completely fills most pages between the lines of text and to the margins.
        Decoration: Decorated initials in red and green on most folios, some of the decoration has faded.
        Binding: 18th-century leather.
        Origin: Written in France, late 13th century (Zacour-Hirsch).
        Cite as:	
        UPenn Ms. Codex 694
        For catalog record, see Permanent Link: 2487484 http://hdl.library.upenn.edu/1017/d/medren/2487484
  For TEI description and digital images, see: http://openn.library.upenn.edu/Data/PennManuscripts/html/mscodex694.html
